"der8auer" or without leet spelled "Der Bauer" does not mean "the fighter". "Bauer" can acutally have a bunch of different meanings, the most common translation would be "farmer", but I guess he is most likely targeting a different meaning :) It can also translate to something like "architect" or "builder", which has much more likely been his intention in my opinion. Although "Bauer" is kind of unusual for the translation to "architect" or "builder", I'd rather call this "Der Erbauer" or something completely different. Maybe it was also meant as a funny ambiguity, I've acutally never read or seen an explanation by der8auer what his intentions were when creating his name.
And your pronunciation is fine, basically correct with an american accent.
